Beijing Marks International Day of Solidarity with Palestine
BEIJING , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The Chinese People 's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries ( CPAFFC ) held a reception here this evening to mark the International Day of Solidarity with Palestine .
Cheng Siwei , vice chairman of the National People 's Congress ( NPC ) Standing Committee , attended the reception along with other senior Chinese officials .
CPAFFC president Qi Huaiyuan said the Chinese people have always supported the just cause of the Palestinian people and have firmly stood beside them .
China will continue to make unremitting efforts to solve the issue of Palestine in the years to come , he said , adding that the Chinese people will be reliable friends of the Palestinian people forever .
He said that the recent accord reached between Palestine and Israel on the second phase of withdrawal of Israeli troops is in the interests of both sides .
It is also of significance for increasing confidence in the peace talks and pushing forward the Middle East peace process , he added .
Qi expressed the hope that both sides will implement the agreements earnestly , and push forward Palestinian-Israeli peace talks and the peace process in order to realize a comprehensive , just and lasting peace at an early date .
Palestinian ambassador to China , Moustapha Saphariny , expressed his gratitude for China 's continuous support for the just cause of the Palestinian people .
He said that the parties will work with the international community to push forward the peace process .
November 29 was designated an International Day of Solidarity with Palestine by the United Nations in a resolution adopted by the UN General Assembly in December 1977 .
